_prev_prog_3.Description:
Prevention Program Description: Toluene diisocyanate (TD) is used for manufacturing of polyurethane products in the facility.  TDI is brought in the facility by trucks in 55-gallon drums.  The trucks enter the facility from one of the gates on Summer Street.  The trucks proceeed to the unloading dock located in the southeast corner of Building 1.  Trained facility operators inspect the drums and then unload in a batch of 4 drums at a time from the trucks and transport these drums via forklift to the Warm Room, which is the designated storage area for TDI.  TDI is stored in this room on pallettes and the room is maintained at adequate temperature to prevent solidification of TDI.     



TDI is used in any of the five reactors U3, U5, U6, U8, and U19.  The process in this reactors are batch processes.  When the process is started, various other raw materisals (both liquid and solid) are filled in the reactor.  TDI drums are taken out of the Warm Room on forklifts by trained operators, hoisted to the mazannaine floor above the reactors by a hoist, and then fed to the opening on the top of tthe reactor by gravity.  TDI is mostly consumed in the process and the product contains less than 1% by weight of TDI.                                    



The facility has developed a process safety management (PSM) program for toxics and flammable substances handled and processed in the facility.  This prevention program is applicable to TDI also.  Specifically for TDI, the prevention programs elements include: 

Detailed process safety information (PSI) for all areas where TDI is handled, stored, or used;

Process hazard analysis (PHA) for all areas where TDI is handled, stored, or used;

Safe operating procedures for handling, storage and movement of TDI within building;

Mechanical integrity program including preventive maintenance for TDI handling equipment;

Incident reporting and investigation program for the facility;

Pre-startup safety review program;

Management of change program;

Emergency response plan for the facility;

Training to operators handling TDI;

Contractor safety program

Hot work permit program; and

Inspection and audit program;

